author: Shira Feder
title: The coronavirus has thick spikes that seem to latch more easily onto human cells than other viruses, according to a 3D map of its structure
description: A new study from the University of Minnesota created a 3D model of the new coronavirus and found that it could bind far more efficiently to human cell receptors than the SARS virus. This might explain how the new coronavirus could spread across the globe at s…
content:
A new study offers fresh insight into the unique structure of the novel coronavirus that makes it so infectious.
